Cybersecurity Incident Report: 
Network Traffic Analysis

Part 1: Provide a summary of the problem found in the DNS and ICMP 
traffic log.


The UDP protocol reveals that:it is a transport layer internet protocol.

This is based on the results of the network analysis, which show that the ICMP echo reply returned the error message: “UDP port 53 unreachable”.

The port noted in the error message is used for: getting the DNS of the domain.

The most likely issue is: it be possible that malicious attack occur at a web server .





